The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 RBI slaps penalty on IDBI

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Mumbai, Aug. 21: The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) today imposed a penalty of Rs 5 lakh on IDBI Ltd for violating its guidelines on opening of accounts, including joint accounts, IPO financing and know your customer norms.

 This penalty was levied under the provisions of section 47 A (1)(b) of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949. The Reserve Bank had issued a show cause notice to the bank in response to which the bank had submitted its written response. Bank chairman V.P. Shetty had also sought personal hearing with the Reserve Bank, which was granted. 

 On careful examination of the banks submission, both oral and written, the RBI came to a conclusion that the violations were substantiated and has accordingly imposed the monetary penalty, a statement said. 




